Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.80,0:00:09.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,The countless flowers,\Nenveloped in light...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.84,0:00:20.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,...gaze at tomorrow\Nwith unwavering eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.46,0:00:39.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,Everyone wishes for me to be pure...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.60,0:00:46.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,...but what can I bring\Nwith me to the frayed skies?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.84,0:00:53.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,What I've made my own\Nby breaking off flowers in bloom...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.18,0:00:59.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,All such sinful things...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.59,0:01:06.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why did I stop making\Npromises with the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.03,0:01:14.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,Because even if I try\Nto run far from all the pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.34,0:01:20.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,...a cold wind rustles\Nmy hair... Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.08,0:01:28.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,Where can I ever find the answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.53,0:01:40.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,Making another unauthorized\Nflight, Chor Tempest?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.93,0:01:42.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Vura!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.47,0:01:48.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Dux Guragief ordered us to go\Non a special training mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.14,0:01:51.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're all busy with\Nregular duties, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.41,0:01:56.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're tired. Night patrol requires\Nfar more vigilance than day patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.54,0:01:58.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,And enemy encounters are likelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.08,0:02:02.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's easier to just float\Naround during the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.92,0:02:09.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,But your chor used to do\Nnothing but daytime patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.06,0:02:13.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,The night shift was always our job.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.36,0:02:15.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,But that's not the case now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.06,0:02:20.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,The top chor on\NArcus Prima is now us, Rubor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.14,0:02:24.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you don't like it,\Nthen prove you're still worthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.34,0:02:27.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,Step aside. We're exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.38,0:02:30.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Everyone, let them pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.55,0:02:38.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,By the way, which Ri Majon?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.39,0:02:41.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Dandelion Ri Majon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.36,0:02:42.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,Dandelion?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.53,0:02:47.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,The ceremonial Ri Majon\Nused for diplomatic purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.13,0:02:50.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why use\Nan old-fashioned Ri Majon like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.63,0:02:53.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,Vura!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.44,0:02:58.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,Help yourself to\Nthe leftover candy on my desk!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.94,0:03:01.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don't wake me coming back!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.24,0:03:07.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,Over International Waters
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.64,0:03:31.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,Wow!\NLook how spotless you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.94,0:03:37.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,These kids worked hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.95,0:03:41.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's quite an antique,\Nso they had a rough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.48,0:03:43.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.35,0:03:47.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,My grandpa flew this\Nwhen he was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.49,0:03:50.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,Your grandfather\Nwas a Simoun sibylla too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.09,0:03:55.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,So after he went to the Spring and\Nstopped flying, he still treasured this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.52,0:04:25.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,They're jealous that we always\Nused to be assigned night patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.53,0:04:30.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,When Chor Rubor used to run into\NNeviril, they'd just look on from afar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.63,0:04:32.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,Be proud of yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:39.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,As a member of Chor Tempest, I plan\Nto take this chor right back to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.78,0:04:45.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right. As far as wanting to see\NTempest back on top, I'm with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.91,0:04:47.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.95,0:04:51.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,Since we won't have to go to the\NSpring as long as we keep winning?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.02,0:04:54.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, I can't wait to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.19,0:04:57.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then what's stopping you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.79,0:05:01.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,I want to go with\Nthe person I care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.56,0:05:05.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then when I emerge from\Nthe Spring, I'll be a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.30,0:05:07.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,And she'll be a woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.64,0:05:10.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,And you'll consummate\Nthings then and there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.07,0:05:13.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,Quiet down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.61,0:05:16.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,Listen up, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.11,0:05:21.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,There are two obstacles\Nto becoming the best chor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.02,0:05:24.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,Unless we get two new members...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.42,0:05:27.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,...we won't be able\Nto fly six Simouns at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.86,0:05:30.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,What's the other thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.49,0:05:32.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.09,0:05:35.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,If Neviril and Aer flew as a pair...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:39.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,...it wouldn't be a stretch\Nto see our chor back on top!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.64,0:05:41.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,Para-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.24,0:05:44.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,...you're giving up on Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.94,0:05:51.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let's do it in front of the Arcus Prima!\NSo that the dux and Neviril can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.06,0:06:09.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Morinas-san, higher!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.50,0:06:12.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Am I not good enough\Nfor Sibylla Aurea?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:14.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,Morinas-san, please concentrate!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.77,0:06:16.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.17,0:06:18.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,You have to lead the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.51,0:06:19.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.81,0:06:21.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,So who's this loved one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.98,0:06:25.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,Floe, I'm hearing bad\Nthings about you lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.48,0:06:28.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,No way! It's not true, is it, Alty?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.82,0:06:30.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,Of course it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.75,0:06:32.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm so happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.19,0:06:35.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Para-sama,\Nyou're responding to my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.56,0:06:37.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.43,0:06:39.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,I was sure you hated me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.99,0:06:41.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,Since the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.90,0:06:43.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Be specific!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.50,0:06:44.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.88,0:06:58.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,Arcus Niger? We're not\Nsupposed to rendezvous till later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.48,0:07:00.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's the Niger. No mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.35,0:07:05.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,An emergency, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.59,0:07:08.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they're just being\Nrushed by the higher-ups.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.72,0:07:11.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,You should summon\Nthe Tempest girls back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.60,0:07:18.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Arcus Niger!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.10,0:07:19.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Niger?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.10,0:07:22.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,They're supposed to be west\Nof the great temple... Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.68,0:07:34.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,A Simile Simoun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.52,0:07:36.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,A messenger?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.92,0:07:40.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,Even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.53,0:07:48.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,How lame is that pilot?\NMissing the cable like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.13,0:07:51.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,No, they're avoiding it on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.14,0:07:55.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.04,0:07:59.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.48,0:08:01.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,Talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.61,0:08:07.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to be Chor Tempest?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.86,0:09:01.27,Regular,,0,0,0,,Since the Plumbum highlands and\Nour nation share similar customs...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.37,0:09:04.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,...I didn't think the decor\Nhere would offend you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.67,0:09:08.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let's have\NTempus Spatium be scarce.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.68,0:09:12.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,That would undermine\Nour authority severely...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.71,0:09:15.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,The highlanders worship\Na deity named Animus.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.25,0:09:17.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,Historically speaking...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.95,0:09:22.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,...Animus and Tempus Spatium\Nare in fact the same god.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.89,0:09:26.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,The highlands and Kyuukoku\Ndo not acknowledge this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.73,0:09:29.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's best to avoid\Nunnecessary stimulation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.86,0:09:32.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,For the sake of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.97,0:09:35.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,Tempus Spatium would\Nbe glad to be concealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.73,0:10:07.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Peace conference?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.90,0:10:14.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right. It's fair to say we're battling\Nall our neighboring countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.58,0:10:16.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Each one,\Nbecause of economic strife...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.28,0:10:20.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,They want the Simouns.\NNo matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.48,0:10:21.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.92,0:10:25.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,To be more precise,\Nthey're after the helical motors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:29.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,Unearthed only from ruins,\Nthe wings that give Simouns flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.06,0:10:35.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,But now the Plumbum highlands\Nhave come to broker a peace deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.76,0:10:40.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's been decided the first conference\Nwill be held in international waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.74,0:10:43.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,In utmost secrecy of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.44,0:10:47.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,So they'll hold this conference\Non the Arcus Prima, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.21,0:10:51.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Who cares about politics?\NAre we free to use the maju pool?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.98,0:10:54.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,I think they'll say not\Nto act without permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.88,0:10:56.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.75,0:11:00.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,The ones flying that Simile before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.55,0:11:03.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why are they\Nwandering around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.57,0:11:15.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,They're headed this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.47,0:11:17.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why are they on our ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.84,0:11:21.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,The most obvious reason is\Nthat they're new members...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.61,0:11:27.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, I bet she'll say something like,\N"Chor Tempest sure is a letdown."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.25,0:11:29.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.32,0:11:36.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sorry for earlier,\Nmembers of Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.59,0:11:39.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,So it was you two after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.96,0:11:42.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,Still, you sure are a letdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.08,0:11:58.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is it that funny, my lady Roatreamon?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.12,0:12:04.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't blame you\Nfor not remembering.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.82,0:12:07.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,I just lived on your estate...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.06,0:12:11.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,...as the daughter of two\Nof your many servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.35,0:12:35.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,Come now, Mamina.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.69,0:12:44.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.53,0:12:49.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am honored that\Nyou remember me, my lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.24,0:12:57.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,As of today,\NI've been ordered to transfer...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.71,0:13:01.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,...from Arcus Niger's\NChor Ignus to Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.11,0:13:05.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm Sibylla Mamina. I'm pleased\Nto make your acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.41,0:13:09.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,And I'm Yun.\NI'm also joining Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.25,0:13:14.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,I have one thing to say. I despise war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.36,0:13:15.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.19,0:13:22.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,Somebody!\NSomebody, please help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.00,0:13:25.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:27.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,What's this about Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.45,0:13:41.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.65,0:13:42.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,Paraietta...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.52,0:13:47.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,What's going on?\NWhat do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.15,0:13:49.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea sleeps\Nalone in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.02,0:13:53.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's a privilege\Ngranted to her alone! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.46,0:13:55.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,Starting today,\Nshe's sharing her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.90,0:13:57.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.10,0:14:00.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Para, it's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.23,0:14:03.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, it has, Vice Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.64,0:14:09.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, I think this is a good way to\Nimmediately bond with your new pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.91,0:14:11.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,New pair?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.58,0:14:14.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then that's my bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.88,0:14:17.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,A "new pair"...Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.09,0:14:20.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm assigning Mamina.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.99,0:14:23.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.59,0:14:25.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.07,0:14:37.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,Pairs should be formed out of mutual\Nneed and according to the natural flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.47,0:14:42.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,You were once a sibylla, Father,\Nso you should be well aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.48,0:14:47.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, in this day and age,\Nit doesn't work that way anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.45,0:14:52.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,You must take this step now\Nor your name will be tarnished.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.92,0:14:56.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,I was an auriga,\Nbut if I can pair with you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.52,0:14:59.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,...I'd be happy to fly as a sagitta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.26,0:15:05.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina is not from\Na family befitting a sibylla.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.60,0:15:11.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,But of all the great temple's\Ncandidates, she scored the highest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.11,0:15:14.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,As far as the Wave Crest\Nand Tsunami Ri Majons...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.31,0:15:16.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,...I can pray better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.18,0:15:19.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,Those are all highly dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.68,0:15:23.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,Which enable us to annihilate\Nmore enemies in one blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.65,0:15:26.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,All I want is for you to snap out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.62,0:15:28.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,Granted, a tragedy occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.82,0:15:35.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,But you shall overcome that and\Nregain your glory as Sibylla Aurea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.93,0:15:40.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,Meaning that your standing in\Nthe council will be safe, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.57,0:15:44.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't understand what's\Ngoing on in your head, Neviril.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.17,0:15:48.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you're put off by battle,\Nthen you should go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.28,0:15:51.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,You'll surely become a lovely woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.51,0:15:57.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,But if you're put off by the Spring and\Nrefuse to fly a Simoun, what then?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.48,0:16:00.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're telling me\Nto give you an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.12,0:16:04.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're old enough now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.63,0:16:06.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is Neviril coming back?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.99,0:16:10.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, Aer, you should\Npair with me after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.57,0:16:13.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,I like Neviril.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.20,0:16:18.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril really is popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.47,0:16:21.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,I think I'll give up on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.88,0:16:23.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.74,0:16:27.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'll pair with someone. But even so,\NI'll still despise what we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.22,0:16:31.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,If so, then just hurry on to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.59,0:16:33.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,I couldn't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.82,0:16:38.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,Already, many of my friends,\Ndespite being priestesses...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.83,0:16:43.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,...were sent to the battlefield since\Nthey could fly Simouns and perished.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.23,0:16:47.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,I couldn't run away\Nfrom that just on my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.80,0:16:50.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,That reason sounds like a death wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.61,0:17:00.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,Paraietta.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.05,0:17:06.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,I always thought you and Neviril\Nwould fly as a pair one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.39,0:17:08.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,Vice Chancellor...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.22,0:17:11.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,No matter what, I will protect Neviril.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.53,0:17:55.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.20,0:17:57.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm still...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.38,0:18:06.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea,\NI want you to be my pair...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.81,0:18:08.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,...body and soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.29,0:18:15.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Mamina, even if you\Ntake my body by force...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.19,0:18:18.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,...you will never be my pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.76,0:18:21.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, try to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.43,0:18:25.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,I've got to pair up with you,\Nno matter what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.52,0:18:49.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.53,0:18:57.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,You actually used that rope\Nto come through the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.83,0:19:00.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're such a funny girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:09.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,All six Simouns will be needed\Nfor the Dandelion Ri Majon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.21,0:19:11.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,As Chor Tempest is now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.48,0:19:15.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,We've already bolstered the ranks.\NIs that not enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.72,0:19:19.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's about whether it can be\Ndone with those new members.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.19,0:19:23.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's a prayer for a key event, the\Npeace conference with the highlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.62,0:19:26.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,We cannot risk failure of any kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.69,0:19:31.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,All I'm asking for is a Ri Majon\Nperformed by Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.43,0:19:34.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you cannot comply\Nwith my request...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.00,0:19:37.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.21,0:19:41.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't want my daughter\Nto suffer any more humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.01,0:19:44.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't want her to get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.90,0:20:05.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina! You want to challenge\Nme in the maju pool too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.70,0:20:07.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Challenge you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.97,0:20:10.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,To decide who'll pair up with Neviril.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.64,0:20:13.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's not a matter of challenging you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.78,0:20:20.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.51,0:20:22.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,As long as we have these outfits on...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.05,0:20:27.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,...the helical motors activate, allowing\Nus to float! But if it's removed...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.62,0:20:28.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,You crazy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.79,0:20:30.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,Say you'll give up on her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.59,0:20:32.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.29,0:20:34.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm going to pair with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.36,0:20:36.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,Same for me! But that's up to her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.20,0:20:41.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,You're of low birth and only made it\Nhere because you can fly a Simoun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.74,0:20:44.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,One such as you is unworthy of her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.34,0:20:46.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,The same goes for you too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.48,0:20:55.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.38,0:20:57.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.49,0:21:06.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,As long as such breaches\Nof conduct continue...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.66,0:21:10.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,...we can only conclude\NChor Tempest no longer functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.56,0:21:12.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,By that, do you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.37,0:21:18.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,Once the peace conference\Nis over, I want Chor Tempest...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.87,0:21:21.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,...to disband.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.78,0:21:23.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,Please wait, Vice Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.68,0:21:25.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then what of your daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.08,0:21:27.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.65,0:21:33.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,I can't leave her in this chor. She'll go\Nto the Spring before she's hurt further.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.55,0:21:36.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,U-Um, then what about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.36,0:21:39.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,You've disappointed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.22,0:22:47.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,It is played by my wounds...\Nthe song of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.96,0:22:52.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let it ring out over\Nthe grieving universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.20,0:22:59.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,Can we change tomorrow?\NDon't be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.24,0:23:06.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,I want to let you know\Nhow my heart's overflowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.66,0:23:19.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,"I want to get closer to you."\N"I want to feel your pulse."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.76,0:23:24.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,I was too defiant,\Nand I took the long way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.93,0:23:28.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,The blue moon is swaying silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.94,0:23:32.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,My true heart's desire is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.94,0:23:38.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,I can't reach you.\NMy tears of pain trickle down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.75,0:23:44.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,Soar away into the sky, song of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.35,0:23:47.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,Carrying my love that came too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.79,0:23:53.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,What can I do to change tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.46,0:23:59.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,Just hold on to "now" the way it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.94,0:24:05.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,To Be Continued
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.81,0:24:06.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,To Be Continued\NThe highland priestess named Anglas...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.64,0:24:08.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,The highland priestess named Anglas...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.34,0:24:12.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,...will be staying with\NChor Tempest for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.48,0:24:17.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,Prayer\NNext time on Simoun...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.05,0:24:18.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,Prayer\NPrayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.42,0:24:19.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,Prayer
